name: politico
text:
Listen to POLITICO Dispatch daily for quick, digestible analysis of the latest news on the pandemic, the election, and more. Subscribe today.
https://t.co/DPUpEFlsul https://t.co/hZMfBDDNeQ

name: politico
text: A senior adviser to Trump’s reelection campaign doubled down on baseless allegations leveled by the president that U.S. doctors are inflating coronavirus deaths for profit as the country sees record levels of new infections https://t.co/HC4nCLqTZi

name: politico
text: Florida Republican Sen. Rick Scott says he hopes the state is able to declare a winner of the presidential race on election night https://t.co/TvBEn1nmUa

name: politico
text: This year is the big test: Is Arizona flippable? And what role will Latinos, who are predominantly of Mexican origin, play in making it happen? https://t.co/o93ug9eIEI

name: politico
text: Democrats remain fretful that Black voter participation in Florida will lag as it did four years ago when Donald Trump beat Hillary Clinton in the state https://t.co/ibpOh102Te

name: politico
text: A federal court in Houston is holding an emergency hearing Monday morning over a last-ditch effort by Republicans in Texas to toss out nearly 127,000 ballots in a Democratic-leaning county https://t.co/0NZoTOyEv2

name: politico
text:
Election Day is upon us, and the battle for control of the Senate remains a coin flip. How are the pivotal races playing out? Can the Senate GOP hold the line? Subscribe to Huddle, our play-by-play guide to Congress, for the latest.
https://t.co/dfpSNWPYfR https://t.co/RnHra08YLY

name: politico
text:
Election administrators have been scrambling to prepare for Tuesday ever since the coronavirus turned a series of primaries into disasters this spring. 

Now, all they can do is wait and see if their efforts pay off. https://t.co/PZhaqc3fPd

name: politico
text: Joe Biden’s campaign fundraising efforts have quietly turned toward raising additional money for a possible post-Election Day legal fight with President Donald Trump that could stretch through November https://t.co/KbtQlTRhXV

name: politico
text: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden holds a single-digit lead over President Donald Trump in Pennsylvania, according to a new survey of the swing state that could determine control of the White House https://t.co/8lrFaHfpxx

name: politico
text:
When Republicans seized control of Congress and the White House in 2016, lobbyists with ties to President Donald Trump and powerful GOP lawmakers saw their stock skyrocket. 

Tuesday’s election could sweep all of that away. https://t.co/cZ0Ho5a0Gg

name: politico
text:
Media reports indicate President Trump may try to message false insinuations about which ballots can be counted ahead of what will likely be a lengthy process.

But it's important to remember that states run elections, not candidates or television networks
https://t.co/CAEICj4P00

name: politico
text: Wall Street can handle pretty much any election outcome other than total uncertainty and perhaps protests and violence in the streets. That is the biggest risk.  https://t.co/39gYkgE2GY

name: politico
text: The reality is, we might not know who prevails in the battle for the Senate for several weeks — and maybe even months https://t.co/A07YgyjtRh

name: politico
text:
The early vote, which has hit record levels in many places, looks promising for Joe Biden.

Yet on election eve, no one can say with any certainty if Biden wins by a landslide or Trump ekes out a reelection victory.
https://t.co/lpEhwQupWH

📷 AP https://t.co/08vz5TJRec

name: politico
text:
The reason is that the race remains close in most of the eight swing states we've identified as critical battlegrounds. 

What’s clear, in the final days, is that the election will be decided on a swing state map unlike any from the past. Here's a look 👇 https://t.co/lpEhwQupWH https://t.co/TtSyTBstdR

name: politico
text: Joe Biden may not be making a stop in Arizona in the final days before the election, but he’s doing the next best thing: he’s spending more money in the critical Phoenix media market than anywhere else in the country https://t.co/rjc1srHci5 https://t.co/YE0SgETqTl

name: politico
text: Florida ultimately boils down to 2 big wagers. Dems are betting they can turn out enough new, blue-leaning independent voters — along with more senior citizens than usual. The GOP gamble hinges on turning out their more high-propensity voters. https://t.co/VmDAIlrsMd https://t.co/9ckl6vv3Tw

name: politico
text: Early voting indicates a surge in turnout this year in Georgia, and it’s staked Joe Biden to an early lead. But Republicans remain confident that GOP voters will show up in droves on Nov. 3 to make up the deficit. https://t.co/kQl5ANM8Td https://t.co/JFJ8QqAUng

name: politico
text: The professional Republicans who spent the past 4 years marveling at each and every one of the 10,704 votes that put Trump over the top in Michigan in 2016 had been clinging to hope that he could expand his coalition. They have abandoned any such optimism. https://t.co/rKXxJ1owfd https://t.co/jPxIFSfgqI

name: politico
text: Coronavirus cases are surging. The early vote looks great for Democrats, who have swamped Donald Trump’s ad spending in the state. But the president keeps coming to the state and has strong support in greater Minnesota, so he can’t be counted out. https://t.co/ANx9f5oAQC https://t.co/CTHuOe9zsD

name: politico
text: Donald Trump won North Carolina in 2016 by running up the score in the outer suburbs. The race is so close this time that he can’t afford a drop-off in those places. https://t.co/0bXjZSNinD https://t.co/xWKRkZvRr1

name: politico
text: Many Republicans view Pennsylvania as Donald Trump’s best chance to carry one of the three Rust Belt states that put him in the White House in 2016 — in part because polling shows the race is closer here than in Wisconsin or Michigan. https://t.co/y9FeuiDrKB https://t.co/uMeq2Uu8nA

name: politico
text: The dominant issue in Wisconsin right now is Covid-19. Residents are in the throes of another surge in the deadly pandemic, which reached a crisis point four weeks ago and shows no signs of slowing. Trump has held mega-rallies in the state anyway. https://t.co/PQD8kTWPWP https://t.co/5Ry4yFNl7N

name: politico
text: President Donald Trump suggested he'd soon fire infectious-disease expert Anthony Fauci in rally remarks last night https://t.co/UfEVaYUkvZ https://t.co/gVze6kF5us

name: politico
text: On the eve of Election Day, over 93 million Americans have already cast their ballots. The numbers suggest a historic turnout, even with comparably low turnout expected in-person on Nov. 3.  https://t.co/MhKNjhqrAa https://t.co/VnqvVllMHM

name: politico
text:
No matter who wins this week, a lot will change in Washington during the coming months. Keep up with the appointments, the people, and the power centers of the next administration with our Transition Playbook. Subscribe today.
https://t.co/0fP2W0nPkz https://t.co/5or9M2wIpQ

name: politico
text: With Pennsylvania looking like the center of the political universe, here’s a guide to the places Trump and Biden are campaigning, and why 👇 https://t.co/bDK296DBw0

name: politico
text:
Erie: The little-known county might be the biggest bellwether in the state: In 2016, it went for Trump by only 2 points.

Erie is a predominantly white, blue-collar area that was once a Democratic stronghold with a proud labor tradition. https://t.co/bDK296DBw0

name: politico
text:
A Muhlenberg College/Morning Call poll found Trump performing better in the northeast than any other part of the state, leading Biden 55-39.

Biden is looking to narrow losses and do better in than Clinton did in 2016, in part by using his hometown appeal. https://t.co/bDK296Vcny

name: politico
text:
There’s no doubt that Biden will sweep Philadelphia and its surrounding suburbs. The question is by how much.
https://t.co/bDK296DBw0

name: politico
text:
Southwestern Pennsylvania is to Trump what the Philadelphia region is to Biden: Outside of Pittsburgh’s Allegheny County, it’s Trump Country. But margins matter — and Biden is trying to cut into the amount by which Trump wins here.
https://t.co/bDK296DBw0

name: politico
text: Lancaster, home to scrapple, dairy farms and the state’s Amish community, has long been a GOP bastion. But it is diversifying and ever so slowly becoming more Democratic. For Biden, the goal isn’t necessarily winning here but chipping into Trump’s lead. https://t.co/bDK296DBw0

name: politico
text: Home to Pittsburgh, the second biggest city in the state, Allegheny County is another tranche of Democratic votes. The city is also surrounded by well-educated, wealthy suburbs where Democrats like their chances. https://t.co/bDK296DBw0

name: politico
text: Trump is pulling out all the stops to show how much he supports fracking. Over the weekend, he directed his administration to study the potential economic impacts of a nationwide ban on fracking. https://t.co/9U5qwEbvOJ

name: politico
text: President Trump is putting in another whirlwind day on the road, with five stops in North Carolina, Pennsylvania, Wisconsin and Michigan. But the big questions left about his activities are about what happens after the polls close, not before. https://t.co/5g5U2K3IOK

name: politico
text: Trade experts say there’s only one thing at stake in Tuesday’s election — everything https://t.co/xHr9FKeweP

name: politico
text:
Democrat congressional candidate Amy Kennedy said today that she is canceling all of her in-person campaign events after interacting with someone during an event on Saturday who has since tested positive for the coronavirus

https://t.co/Ed2FNUeTbt

name: politico
text: For farmers and ranchers, Biden’s approach to tariffs and trade could be easier on their bottom lines after Trump’s multiyear battles with China and other partners — but he might not offer the same direct taxpayer support that Trump handed to the industry https://t.co/I8THHhntYH

name: politico
text: Most eyes will be on the presidency and the possibility of a Senate flip tomorrow, but there are some other significant races in the mix that could shift the power structure of transportation policy in D.C. Here are some of the vulnerable sitting members 👇https://t.co/Tmn1BfcfVc

name: politico
text:
Colombia’s drug policy will not be top of mind for most Americans heading to the polls, but for Colombians, the future of U.S. foreign policy in the region has serious consequences

https://t.co/bhQwhK8Ktk

name: politico
text: 2020 has been a dark year as smaller oil producers have packed up and left their wells and crude prices sank to unprofitable territory. On POLITICO Energy, @dailym1 explains how Exxon and Chevron are taking drastic actions to  survive the economic crisis. https://t.co/Yb2Utos9cX

name: politico
text:
Joe Biden has a single-digit lead in Pennsylvania and is in a dead heat with Donald Trump in Arizona, according to new surveys of the pair of swing states

https://t.co/bnRfvE3ITx

name: politico
text:
Joe Biden has a narrow lead in the key states of Florida and Ohio, according to a Quinnipiac poll published just today.

In Florida, 47% of likely voters support Biden, while 42% support Donald Trump. In Ohio, 47% support Biden and 43% support Trump
https://t.co/OWreXhFkxj

name: politico
text:
A federal judge in Houston has turned aside a push by Republicans to toss out nearly 127,000 ballots cast by drive-through voting in recent days in the state’s largest county, which is a major Democratic stronghold

https://t.co/0NZoTOyEv2

name: politico
text:
Gavin Newsom’s highest-profile moments in the 2020 election have featured him effusively praising the work of Donald Trump — or at least declining to lay into the president.

But behind the scenes, Newsom has been raising millions of dollars to oust Trump
https://t.co/aBhRh8phJv

name: politico
text:
Nancy Pelosi said Dems will deploy budget reconciliation procedures next year to enhance the Affordable Care Act and provide more pandemic relief if the party secures a narrow majority in the Senate, wins the White House and maintains control of the House
https://t.co/nI34Pag0N5

name: politico
text:
Spend election night with us: Our reporters will break down how the race to 270 is looking so far, discuss any notable exit poll readouts and analyze the closing Trump and Biden strategies. 

Tune in to our “Foursquare” show live at 9 p.m. ET tomorrow: https://t.co/8thKRMIWNc https://t.co/dl7gSEPUq1

name: politico
text: Any specific questions you'd love our reporters @TimAlberta, @lbarronlopez, @EugeneDaniels2 and @RyanLizza to addre… https://t.co/TqhP46gEZq

name: politico
text:
Only 17% of voters expect the winner of the presidential election to be announced on Tuesday night, according to our new poll with Morning Consult
https://t.co/ByvuB66Om8
